checks — fixed\n- MEDIUM: Schema `additionalProperties: false` on `score` and `evidence` but `true` on findings/top-level, causing inconsistent forward-compatibility — fixed\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- LOW: `buildAllUnknownVerdict` takes `WorkItem[]` but only uses `.length` — parameter type could be `number` for clarity\n- LOW: `parseVerdict` always throws `retryable: true` (stateless), deviating from AC#5/AC#6 which specify different values per call count — functionally correct but spec says parser should throw `retryable: false` on second attempt. Parser is stateless so it cannot track this. Engine handles it correctly regardless.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None below floor. Branch coverage on verdict-parser.ts was 86.95% (now improved with added tests). Remaining uncovered branches are Ajv internal error formatting edge cases (`err.message` being undefined).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The retry orchestration design is sound (stateless parser, stateful engine). The deviation from AC#5/AC#6 on `retryable` values is a spec-vs-implementation mismatch that doesn't affect behavior.\n- `buildAllUnknownVerdict` generates synthetic AC indices (1, 2, 3...) that don't correspond to actual story ACs — downstream consumers should be aware these are placeholder indices.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 8, Edit: 5, Grep: 3, Glob: 2, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` full suite (~15 lines), `npm run build` (~10 lines), `git diff --name-only HEAD` (~15 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: one re-read of `verdict.schema.json` that returned cached result; one redundant grep for coverage output that returned empty"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3953cce470cb24fd (use SendMessage with to: 'a3953cce470cb24fd' to continue this agent)\n<usage>tota