{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SVRHYppJQxV8aCUbSThRBb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 6.2: Evaluator Verdict JSON Schema & Parsing\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want the evaluator verdict validated against a JSON schema with robust parsing and retry,\n11\tso that every AC has a reliable status and evidence — and malformed output never silently passes.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** `src/schemas/verdict.schema.json` exists\n16\t   **When** inspected\n17\t   **Then** it defines the `EvaluatorVerdict` structure: top-level `verdict` (pass|fail), `score` object (passed, failed, unknown, total — all integers >= 0), `findings` array where each item has `ac` (integer), `description` (string), `status` (pass|fail|unknown), and `evidence` object with `commands_run` (array of strings), `output_observed` (string), and `reasoning` (string), plus optional `evaluator_trace_id` (string) and `duration_seconds` (number)\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** the verdict schema exists\n21\t   **When** validated with a valid EvaluatorVerdict JSON\n22\t   **Then** validation passes with no errors\n23\t   **And** when validated with missing required fields, invalid field types, or extra `status` enum values, validation returns specific error messages identifying the violation\n24\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n25\t\n26\t3. **Given** `src/lib/verdict-parser.ts` exists\n27\t   **When** inspected\n28\t   **Then** it exports `parseVerdict(output: string): EvaluatorVerdict` and `validateVerdict(data: unknown): VerdictValidationResult`\n29\t   **And** `VerdictValidationResult` includes `valid: boolean`, `errors?: string[]`, and `verdict?: EvaluatorVerdict`\n30\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n31\t\n32\t4. **Given** an evaluator returns valid JSON matching the verdict schema\n33\t   **When** `parseVerdict(output)` is called\n34\t   **Then** it returns a fully typed `EvaluatorVerdict` object with all fields populated\n35\t   **And** every finding with `status: 'pass'` has non-empty `evidence.commands_run` (at least one command string) — if a PASS finding has empty `commands_run`, the finding is downgraded to `status: 'unknown'` with reasoning appended\n36\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n37\t\n38\t5. **Given** an evaluator returns malformed or non-JSON output\n39\t   **When** `parseVerdict(output)` is called the first time\n40\t   **Then** it throws a `VerdictParseError` with `retryable: true` and the raw output attached\n41\t   **And** the caller (workflow engine) re-dispatches the evaluator for one retry attempt\n42\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n43\t\n44\t6. **Given** the evaluator's retry also returns malformed output\n45\t   **When** `parseVerdict(output)` is called the second time\n46\t   **Then** it throws a `VerdictParseError` with `retryable: false`\n47\t   **And** the caller produces an all-UNKNOWN `EvaluatorVerdict` with `reasoning: \"Evaluator failed to produce valid JSON after retry\"`\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t7. **Given** `VerdictParseError` class in `verdict-parser.ts`\n51\t   **When** inspected\n52\t   **Then** it extends `Error` and has fields: `retryable: boolean`, `rawOutput: string`, and `validationErrors?: string[]`\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t8. **Given** the existing `parseVerdict()` and `EvaluatorVerdict` in `workflow-engine.ts`\n56\t   **When** the new `verdict-parser.ts` module is complete\n57\t   **Then** `workflow-engine.ts` imports `parseVerdict` and `EvaluatorVerdict` from `verdict-parser.ts` instead of defining them locally\n58\t   **And** the inline `parseVerdict` function and `EvaluatorVerdict` interface are removed from `workflow-engine.ts`\n59\t   **And** all existing callers of `parseVerdict` and users of `EvaluatorVerdict` continue to compile and pass tests\n60\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n61\t\n62\t9. **Given** unit tests for `verdict-parser.ts`\n63\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n64\t   **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for `verdict-parser.ts` covering: valid verdict parsing, schema validation pass/fail, PASS-without-evidence downgrade, malformed JSON error with retryable=true, second-failure error with retryable=false, VerdictParseError shape, and edge cases (empty string, partial JSON, extra fields ignored)\n65\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n66\t\n67\t10. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n68\t    **When** the build completes\n69\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero errors\n70\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n71\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n72\t\n73\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n74\t\n75\t- [x] Task 1: Create verdict JSON schema (AC: #1, #2)\n76\t  - [x] Create `src/schemas/verdict.schema.json` with full EvaluatorVerdict structure\n77\t  - [x] Define `verdict` enum: pass, fail\n78\t  - [x] Define `score` object with integer constraints (minimum: 0)\n79\t  - [x] Define `findings` array with per-AC structure: ac, description, status, evidence\n80\t  - [x] Define `evidence` object: commands_run (array of strings), output_observed (string), reasoning (string)\n81\t  - [x] Define optional fields: evaluator_trace_id, duration_seconds\n82\t  - [x] Write schema validation tests (valid cases, missing fields, wrong types, bad enum values)\n83\t\n84\t- [x] Task 2: Create verdict-parser module (AC: #3, #4, #7)\n85\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/verdict-parser.ts`\n86\t  - [x] Define `VerdictValidationResult` interface\n87\t  - [x] Define `VerdictParseError` class extending Error with `retryable`, `rawOutput`, `validationErrors`\n88\t  - [x] Implement `validateVerdict(data: unknown)` — validate against JSON schema using Ajv\n89\t  - [x] Implement `parseVerdict(output: string)` — JSON.parse, validate, enforce PASS-evidence invariant\n90\t  - [x] PASS-evidence enforcement: if a finding has `status: 'pass'` and `commands_run` is empty, downgrade to `status: 'unknown'` with reasoning appended\n91\t\n92\t- [x] Task 3: Implement retry semantics in parseVerdict (AC: #5, #6)\n93\t  - [x] On invalid JSON or schema validation failure, throw `VerdictParseError` with `retryable: true`\n94\t  - [x] The retry orchestration itself lives in the caller (workflow-engine) — `verdict-parser` only signals retryability\n95\t  - [x] Document that after the caller's single retry, a second `VerdictParseError` should be caught and an all-UNKNOWN verdict generated\n96\t\n97\t- [x] Task 4: Migrate workflow-engine.ts (AC: #8)\n98\t  - [x] Remove inline `EvaluatorVerdict` interface from `workflow-engine.ts`\n99\t  - [x] Remove inline `parseVerdict()` function from `workflow-engine.ts`\n100\t  - [x] Add `import { parseVerdict, EvaluatorVerdict } from './verdict-parser.js'`\n101\t  - [x] Update `parseVerdict` call site: wrap in try/catch for `VerdictParseError`, implement single-retry logic\n102\t  - [x] Re-export `EvaluatorVerdict` from `workflow-engine.ts` if other modules import it from there (check `buildRetryPrompt`, `filterRetryItems`)\n103\t  - [x] Verify all existing imports still resolve\n104\t\n105\t- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #9, #10)\n106\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/verdict-parser.test.ts`\n107\t  - [x] Test: valid verdict parses correctly\n108\t  - [x] Test: schema validation rejects missing verdict field\n109\t  - [x] Test: schema validation rejects invalid status enum\n110\t  - [x] Test: PASS finding with empty commands_run downgraded to UNKNOWN\n111\t  - [x] Test: PASS finding with non-empty commands_run stays PASS\n112\t  - [x] Test: malformed JSON throws VerdictParseError with retryable=true\n113\t  - [x] Test: empty string throws VerdictParseError with retryable=true\n114\t  - [x] Test: partial JSON throws VerdictParseError with retryable=true\n115\t  - [x] Test: extra fields in verdict are tolerated (not rejected)\n116\t  - [x] Test: VerdictParseError has correct shape (retryable, rawOutput, validationErrors)\n117\t  - [x] Test: validateVerdict returns specific error messages for each violation\n118\t  - [x] Verify existing workflow-engine tests still pass after migration\n119\t  - [x] Verify 80%+ coverage on verdict-parser.ts\n120\t\n121\t## Dev Notes\n122\t\n123\t### Module Design\n124\t\n125\t`verdict-parser.ts` is a focused module responsible for:\n126\t1. Validating evaluator output against the verdict JSON schema\n127\t2. Enforcing the PASS-evidence invariant (no evidence = downgrade to UNKNOWN)\n128\t3. Signaling retry semantics via `VerdictParseError.retryable`\n129\t\n130\tIt does NOT orchestrate retries — the workflow engine decides when to re-dispatch the evaluator. The parser only says \"this is invalid and retryable\" or \"this is invalid and not retryable.\"\n131\t\n132\t### Integration Points\n133\t\n134\t- `src/schemas/verdict.schema.json` — the schema file, loaded at module init\n135\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — current home of `parseVerdict()` and `EvaluatorVerdict` (to be migrated)\n136\t- `src/lib/evaluator.ts` — returns raw `EvaluatorResult.output` that this module parses\n137\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` lines 568-618 — the verify task result handling that calls `parseVerdict()` and uses the verdict\n138\t\n139\t### Data Flow\n140\t\n141\t```\n142\tEvaluatorResult.output (raw string from story 6-1)\n143\t  → parseVerdict(output)\n144\t    → JSON.parse\n145\t    → validateVerdict (schema check via Ajv)\n146\t    → enforce PASS-evidence invariant\n147\t    → return typed EvaluatorVerdict\n148\t  OR\n149\t    → throw VerdictParseError(retryable: true) on first failure\n150\t    → caller re-dispatches evaluator\n151\t    → parseVerdict(retryOutput)\n152\t    → throw VerdictParseError(retryable: false) on second failure\n153\t    → caller generates all-UNKNOWN verdict\n154\t```\n155\t\n156\t### Existing Code to Migrate\n157\t\n158\tThe current `parseVerdict()` in `workflow-engine.ts` (lines 373-396) does basic JSON parsing with manual field checks but:\n159\t- Does NOT validate against a JSON schema\n160\t- Does NOT enforce PASS-evidence invariant\n161\t- Returns `null` on failure instead of throwing with retry semantics\n162\t- Has no `VerdictParseError` type\n163\t\n164\tThe migration must preserve backward compatibility: `buildRetryPrompt()` and `filterRetryItems()` in `workflow-engine.ts` both depend on `EvaluatorVerdict` and `parseVerdict()`. After migration, re-export `EvaluatorVerdict` from `workflow-engine.ts` to avoid breaking downstream imports.\n165\t\n166\t### Schema Validation Library\n167\t\n168\tUse **Ajv** (Already JSON Schema Validator). Check if Ajv is already in `package.json`. If not, add `ajv` as a dependency. Use `draft-07` to match the existing schema files (`workflow.schema.json` and `agent.schema.json` both use `draft-07`).\n169\t\n170\t### PASS-Evidence Invariant (FR26)\n171\t\n172\tPer AD5 in architecture-v2.md: \"Every PASS has non-empty evidence.commands_run.\" This is not just a schema constraint — it's a runtime enforcement rule. If the evaluator says PASS but provides no commands, the parser downgrades the finding to UNKNOWN. This prevents the evaluator from lying about verification.\n173\t\n174\tImplementation:\n175\t```typescript\n176\tfor (const finding of verdict.findings) {\n177\t  if (finding.status === 'pass' && (!finding.evidence.commands_run || finding.evidence.commands_run.length === 0)) {\n178\t    finding.status = 'unknown';\n179\t    finding.evidence.reasoning += ' [Downgraded from PASS: no commands_run evidence provided]';\n180\t  }\n181\t}\n182\t```\n183\t\n184\tAfter downgrading, recalculate `verdict.score` counts and potentially flip `verdict.verdict` to `'fail'` if no PASSes remain.\n185\t\n186\t### Retry Semantics\n187\t\n188\tThe parser throws `VerdictParseError` with `retryable: true` on first parse failure. The workflow engine's verify task handler (around line 578) must be updated:\n189\t\n190\t```\n191\ttry {\n192\t  verdict = parseVerdict(dispatchResult.output);\n193\t} catch (err) {\n194\t  if (err instanceof VerdictParseError && err.retryable) {\n195\t    // Re-dispatch evaluator (one retry)\n196\t    const retryResult = await dispatchAgent(...);\n197\t    try {\n198\t      verdict = parseVerdict(retryResult.output);\n199\t    } catch {\n200\t      // Generate all-UNKNOWN verdict\n201\t      verdict = buildAllUnknownVerdict(storyFiles, 'Evaluator failed to produce valid JSON after retry');\n202\t    }\n203\t  }\n204\t}\n205\t```\n206\t\n207\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n208\t\n209\t- **Do NOT use regex to parse verdict JSON** — use JSON.parse + schema validation\n210\t- **Do NOT silently accept malformed verdicts** — the old `parseVerdict` returns null; the new one throws with context\n211\t- **Do NOT validate schema at every call** — compile the Ajv validator once at module load\n212\t- **Do NOT put retry orchestration in the parser** — parser signals retryability, engine orchestrates\n213\t- **Do NOT modify the `evaluator.ts` module** — it returns raw output; parsing is this module's job\n214\t- **Do NOT change the EvaluatorVerdict interface shape** — it matches AD5 and is used by workflow-engine, circuit-breaker (Epic 7) will depend on it\n215\t\n216\t### Project Structure Notes\n217\t\n218\t- New file: `src/schemas/verdict.schema.json` — JSON schema for evaluator verdict\n219\t- New file: `src/lib/verdict-parser.ts` — verdict parsing and validation\n220\t- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/verdict-parser.test.ts`\n221\t- Modified file: `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — remove inline parseVerdict/EvaluatorVerdict, import from verdict-parser\n222\t- May need: `npm install ajv` if not already a dependency (check `package.json`)\n223\t\n224\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n225\t\n226\tFrom story 6-1 (evaluator module):\n227\t- `runEvaluator()` returns `EvaluatorResult` with `output: string` — this is the raw string we parse\n228\t- `buildUnknownOutput()` in `evaluator.ts` generates fallback JSON matching the EvaluatorVerdict shape — the schema must accept this format\n229\t- Timeout and Docker-unavailable cases already produce well-formed UNKNOWN verdicts — our parser should accept these\n230\t- `evaluator.ts` is additive-only; do NOT modify it in this story\n231\t\n232\tFrom story 5-2 (loop blocks):\n233\t- The workflow engine's loop handler calls `parseVerdict()` and uses the result to determine retry items\n234\t- `filterRetryItems()` depends on `EvaluatorVerdict` to decide which stories need retry\n235\t- `buildRetryPrompt()` depends on `EvaluatorVerdict.findings` to inject failure context\n236\t\n237\t### References\n238\t\n239\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 6.2: Evaluator Verdict JSON Schema & Parsing]\n240\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD5: Evaluator Verdict Schema]\n241\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Format Patterns — Evaluator verdict]\n242\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts#EvaluatorVerdict interface (lines 43-63)]\n243\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts#parseVerdict function (lines 373-396)]\n244\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts#buildRetryPrompt (line 405)]\n245\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts#filterRetryItems (line 435)]\n246\t- [Source: src/lib/evaluator.ts#buildUnknownOutput (line 55) — fallback verdict format]\n247\t- [Source: src/schemas/workflow.schema.json — existing schema format reference (draft-07)]\n248\t- [Source: src/schemas/agent.schema.json — existing schema format reference (draft-07)]\n249\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn.md — predecessor story]\n250\t\n251\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n252\t## Verification Requirements\n253\t\n254\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/6-2-evaluator-verdict-json-schema-parsing-proof.md)\n255\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n256\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n257\t\n258\t## Documentation Requirements\n259\t\n260\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n261\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/6-2-evaluator-verdict-json-schema-parsing.md\n262\t\n263\t## Testing Requirements\n264\t\n265\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n266\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n267\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n268\t\n269\t## Dev Agent Record\n270\t\n271\t### Agent Model Used\n272\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n273\t\n274\t### Debug Log References\n275\tN/A\n276\t\n277\t### Completion Notes List\n278\t- Created verdict JSON schema (draft-07) at `src/schemas/verdict.schema.json`\n279\t- Created `src/lib/verdict-parser.ts` with `parseVerdict()`, `validateVerdict()`, `VerdictParseError`, and `EvaluatorVerdict` interface\n280\t- Migrated `EvaluatorVerdict` interface and `parseVerdict()` out of `workflow-engine.ts` with re-exports for backward compatibility\n281\t- Added retry semantics in workflow-engine's verify task handler using `VerdictParseError.retryable`\n282\t- Added `buildAllUnknownVerdict()` helper for fallback after retry failure\n283\t- Updated existing workflow-engine tests to match new throw-on-failure behavior\n284\t- 28 new tests in verdict-parser.test.ts, all passing\n285\t- Coverage: 97.56% statements, 100% lines, 100% functions on verdict-parser.ts\n286\t- All 4086 tests pass, build succeeds with zero errors\n287\t\n288\t### File List\n289\t- `src/schemas/verdict.schema.json` (new)\n290\t- `src/lib/verdict-parser.ts` (new)\n291\t- `src/lib/__tests__/verdict-parser.test.ts` (new)\n292\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` (modified)\n293\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` (modified)\n294\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NQ771iCiXCfQFTaESuSBGk