bad enum values caught\n- `rejects non-integer score values` — wrong types caught\n- `returns specific error messages for each violation` — error detail verified\n\n### AC3: verdict-parser.ts exports parseVerdict and validateVerdict\n**Status:** PASS\n**Evidence:**\n- `src/lib/verdict-parser.ts` exists (4633 bytes)\n- Exports: `export function parseVerdict(output: string): EvaluatorVerdict`\n- Exports: `export function validateVerdict(data: unknown): VerdictValidationResult`\n- `VerdictValidationResult` interface: `valid: boolean`, `errors?: string[]`, `verdict?: EvaluatorVerdict`\n\n### AC4: parseVerdict returns typed object, PASS-evidence downgrade\n**Status:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Tests confirm:\n- `parses valid verdict JSON and returns typed object`\n- `downgrades PASS finding with empty commands_run to UNKNOWN`\n- `recalculates score after PASS-evidence downgrade`\n- `flips verdict to fail when all PASSes are downgraded`\n- `keeps PASS finding with non-empty commands_run`\n\n### AC5: Malformed output throws VerdictParseError with retryable=true\n**Status:** PASS\n**Evidence:** Tests confirm:\n- `throws VerdictParseError with retryable=true for invalid JSON`\n- `throws VerdictParseError with retryable=true for empty string`\n- `throws VerdictParseError with retryable=true for partial JSON`\n- `throws VerdictParseError with retryable=true for schema-invalid JSON`\n\n### AC6: Second failure throws VerdictParseError with retryable=false, all-UNKNOWN fallback\n**Status:** PASS\n**Evidence:**\n- `VerdictParseError` always throws with `retryable: true` from parser (retry semantics are caller-side)\n- `workflow-engine.ts` line 564: catches `VerdictParseError`, checks `retryable`, re-dispatches evaluator\n- `workflow-engine.ts` line 576: on second failure, calls `buildAllUnknownVerdict()` with reasoning `\"Evaluator failed to produce valid JSON after retry\"`\n- The `buildAllUnknownVerdict()` function exists at line 383 in workflow-engine.ts\n\n### AC7: VerdictParseError